{"parentUuid": null, "isSidechain": true, "promptId": "6c3a0b22-aa71-4abe-86b8-7ed7f2e35c75", "agentId": "a132a101ae6f0cefa", "type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "Adversarially verify this finding about the repo at /home/jleechan/projects/ez-gh-actions (public: github.com/jleechanorg/ez-gh-actions, evidence at /home/jleechan/projects/ez-gh-actions/evidence/e2e-20260703, run https://github.com/jleechanorg/ez-gh-actions/actions/runs/28685531107). Try to REFUTE it by reading the actual code/evidence and, where relevant, live gh queries. Finding from \"code-bugs\" (major): Crash-looping runner container leaks unbounded JIT registrations \u2014 no backoff, no visibility, no cleanup\ndocker_backend.rs:66-102, 187-207. `start_one` only cleans up the server-side JIT registration when `docker run` itself exits non-zero (line 91-98). If `docker run -d` succeeds but the container dies immediately afterwards \u2014 wrong-arch image on Apple Silicon, image missing `./run.sh`, expired/garbled jitconfig, OOM during runner bootstrap \u2014 the `--rm` flag erases the container, `managed_containers()` (docker ps, no `-a`) can never observe that it existed, and the offline JIT registration is orphaned on GitHub. The serve loop then sees `alive=0` and spawns a fresh registration+container every 30 seconds with zero backoff: ~2,880 orphaned offline `ezgha-*` registrations per day per configured runner, plus continuous generate-jitconfig API calls burning rate limit. `Status` shows the zombie list growing but nothing reaps them; only a manual `ezgha stop` (which also nukes other hosts, see separate finding) cleans up. The failure is silent from serve's perspective \u2014 it prints 'respawned ephemeral runner X' every cycle as if things were healthy.\nRefute if the factual basis is wrong, the scenario cannot occur, or severity is inflated (severity inflation alone -> not refuted, but say so)."}, "uuid": "a603bb70-e72d-4f19-a883-3bc6bfe0a63e", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T22:21:04.286Z", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner", "sessionId": "8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b", "version": "2.1.198", "gitBranch": "fix/linux-runner-pre-job-hook", "slug": "velvet-wishing-cake"}
